Base.Explanation: Create, update or delete an iProtect account.

Base.Name: Session ID
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the Powershell Agent service session.

Base.Name: iProtect USER webservice url
Base.Description: The address of the iProtect USER webservice. (https://server:8443/Webcontrols/automated/import)

Base.Name: Account operation
Base.Description: Account operation, valid values are: [1, 2, 3] description: (1 = Create account, 2 = Update account, 3 = Delete account).

Base.Name: Salary number
Base.Description: Is a unique identified for that person. This can be a combination of numbers and characters.

Base.Name: Contract end date
Base.Description: Employee contract end date. Correct format: 1967/08/31 00:00:00

Base.Name: Department
Base.Description: Is the name of the department, if the name not exist is the database a new department will be created.

Base.Name: Card type ID
Base.Description: Is the ID of the accesskey type. iProtect can couple many accesskeys of different type to a single person. So only the card number is not enough to uniquely define the card.

Base.Name: Card start date
Base.Description: Start date of the validity period. Correct format: 1967/08/31 00:00:00

Base.Name: Card end date
Base.Description: End date of the validity period. Correct format: 1967/08/31 00:00:00

Base.Name: Activate anti pass-back for this card
Base.Description: Indicates whether anti pass-back should be activated for this card

Base.Name: Activate time anti pass-back for this card
Base.Description: Indicates whether time anti pass-back should be activated for this card

Base.Name: Card isValid
Base.Description: Indicates whether the accesskey is valid. An accesskey is only valid between the start and end date AND when this value is 1.

Base.Name: Card has unlimited access
Base.Description: If this is set to true the start and end date are ignored

Base.Name: Trace enabled
Base.Description: Indicates whether the trace function should be activated for this card.

Base.Name: Card comment
Base.Description: Free text for explanation the reason setting trace function.

Base.Name: Keygroup code
Base.Description: This tag refers to the code of a keygroup that should be defined in the iProtect database. When the accesskey is imported it is placed in this keygroup and gets the access rights accordingly. In this way all imported card can get default access rights.

Base.Name: retVal
Base.Description: This will be 0 when the action executes successfully. If an error occured during execution, the value will be 1.
